	   <tr><td colspan=2>First off, I am not commenting on whether or not Shaman can melee or not. What I am doing is pointing out a false fact in your statement.<br><br>&quot;Now let's take the Rune Etched Icewurm Fang. This puppy in nuts. With a 12/19 and self hasted I can swing insanely fast. This roughly works out to about 2 swings every second.&quot;<br><br>Not possible. 2 swings every second means a delay ratio of roughly 5. No matter what you do, hasted or not hasted, your delay cannot and will not drop below 11. The only case in which this is possible is with the Moss Covered Twig, which starts with 10 delay, but was taken out of the game for that very reason. So no, you cannot swing twice every second. Maybe if you were dual wielding or if you had double attack, but not without either of those.<br><br>And no, I'm not debating that you can or cannot melee.<br>&nbsp;<br>A sunflower scowls at you, ready to attack -- what would you like your tombstone to say?<br>A sunflower kicks YOU for 22 damage!<br><br>Varukisas Jadescale, 40th Iksar Monk<br>Tarew Marr<br>&lt;House of Elder&gt</td></tr>
